The blast took place near a convoy carrying the deputy chairman of Pakistan&#8217;s upper house as it left a mosque. CAPE TOWN - At least 17 people have been killed in an explosion in Pakistan's Balochistan province, which appears to have targeted a top lawmaker. The blast took place near a convoy carrying the deputy chairman of Pakistan s upper house as it left a mosque. Police says it was not clear whether it was a bomb or a suicide attack.Many other people were reported to have been injured in the blast.The most severely injured were air-lifted to hospital in the provincial capital.It s unclear who carried out the attack.